ate-level gay marriage bans.</p></div></article><article class="lead-m"><header><h2 class="title-headline-main"><a href="http://www.christianpost.com/news/poll-for-first-time-majority-of-americans-want-ground-troops-sent-to-fight-isis-134398/">Poll: For First Time, Majority of Americans Want Ground Troops Sent to Fight ISIS</a></h2></header><div class="lead-thumb"><img src="http://images.christianpost.com/full/80112/u-s-soldiers.jpg?w=166&h=103&l=50&t=40" alt="U.S. soldiers" /></div><div class="details"><span class="entry-byline-h">By <a href="/author/stoyan-zaimov/">Stoyan Zaimov</a></span></div><div class="entry-content-h"><p>A CBS News poll has found that for the first time since the U.S. began military operations against ISIS, the majority of Americans want ground troops to be sent to fight the terror group.</p></div></article><article class="lead-m"><header><h2 class="title-headline-main"><a href="http://www.christianpost.com/news/7-homeschool-kids-to-remain-in-state-custody-at-least-5-more-weeks-father-says-theyre-victims-of-christian-persecution-134335/">7 Homeschool Kids to Remain in State Custody at Least 5 More Weeks; Father Says They're Victims of 'Christian Persecution'</a></h2></header><div class="lead-thumb"><img src="http://images.christianpost.com/full/80391/stanley-family-protest-sign.png?w=166&h=103&l=50&t=40" alt="Stanley Family Protest Sign" /></div><div class="details"><span class="entry-byline-h">By <a href="/author/samuel-smith/">Samuel Smith</a></span></div><div class="entry-content-h"><p>After his recent parental custody hearing was postponed for an additional six weeks, the devout Christian father of seven Arkansas homeschool students, who were removed from their home by state and local authorities last month, is claiming that his family is a victim of "Christian persecution."</p></div></article><article class="lead-m"><header><h2 class="title-headline-main"><a href="http://www.christianpost.com/news/will-liberal-professors-wake-up-to-the-d